Package: monpwr
Title: Conditional, Prospective, and Hybrid Power Analysis for Monitoring Programme Design
Version: 0.2.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Ollie", "Gansell", email = "ogansell@doc.govt.nz", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Evaluates statistical power and precision for monitoring programme
    design scenarios. Supports three simulation modes: conditional (plots
    initialised from their existing visit history and BLUP, so the existing
    temporal record contributes to power), prospective (from-scratch, for
    evaluating new designs), and hybrid (a mixture of legacy plots with existing
    records and new plots with no prior visits, each initialised appropriately).
    A standardised parameter-extraction layer (extract_params) dispatches on the
    fitted model class, supporting glmmTMB and lme4 model families out of the
    box; user-supplied extractors and initialisation functions allow any model
    family to be used. Reporting scales are fully user-defined through a named
    list of grouping columns, making the package applicable to any monitoring
    context regardless of response variable, covariate structure, or grouping
    taxonomy. The simulation engine, outer loop, MDC derivation, precision
    estimation, and plotting functions are generic and model-agnostic.
